Name: Sneezing
Description: Sneezing allows your disease to spread easier but also brings it some attention.

Name: Coughing
Description: Coughing allows your disease to spread easier but also brings it some attention.

Name: Nausea
Description: Nausea allows your disease to spread through mouth to mouth contact and draws some attention to it.

Name: Rash
Description: People avoid the infected more but they are more contagious. And more visible.

Name: Dehydration
Description: Dehydration can be deadly and is slightly noticeable.

Name: Vomiting
Description: Vomiting brings a lot of attention but also can make the infected frail and weak.

Name: Dizziness
Description: Dizziness can lead to dangerous accidents!

Name: Fatigue
Description: Fatigue weakens the immune system of the infected.

Name: Fever
Description: Fevers can be deadly.

Name: Diarrhea
Description: Diarrhea and its dehydrating effects can be deadly and can spread infection to the water supply.

Name: Insomnia
Description: Insomnia weakens immune system responses.

Name: Lesions
Description: Lesions can cause open wounds leading to death and spread of infection.

Name: Cysts
Description: Cysts hold pathogens and can burst and spread the disease.

Name: Pulmonary Obstruction
Description: This is a very deadly symptom long term. Limited breathing and lung damage are very visible however.

Name: Inflammation
Description: Inflammation is harmful and disrupting for many bodily processes. Can be deadly

Name: Paralysis
Description: Paralysis is deadly but makes it much less likely for infected to infect others.

Name: Coma
Description: Comas are very deadly and make it much less likely for infected to infect others.

Name: Delirium
Description: Delerium comes after not sleeping for way too long. It is very dangerous and very noticeable.

Name: Pulmonary Edema
Description: Blood in the lungs or Pulmonary Edema makes a disease more infective and deadly and visible.

Name: Hypoxia
Description: Hypoxia or the death of organs due to lack of oxygen is extremely deadly and will lead to much notice.

Name: Heat Resistance I
Description: Resistance to low heat.

Name: Heat Resistance II
Description: Resistance to medium heat.

Name: Heat Resistance III
Description: Resistance to high heat.

Name: Cold Resistance I
Description: Resistance to low cold.

Name: Cold Resistance II
Description: Resistance to medium cold.

Name: Cold Resistance III
Description: Resistance to high cold.

Name: Wet Resistance I
Description: Resistance to low wetness.

Name: Wet Resistance II
Description: Resistance to medium wetness.

Name: Wet Resistance III
Description: Resistance to high wetness.

Name: Dry Resistance I
Description: Resistance to low dryness.

Name: Dry Resistance II
Description: Resistance to medium dryness.

Name: Dry Resistance III
Description: Resistance to high dryness.

Name: Medicinal Resistance I
Description: Resistance to low levels of medicine.

Name: Medicinal Resistance II
Description: Resistance to medium levels of medicine.

Name: Medicinal Resistance III
Description: Resistance to high levels of medicine.

Name: Water Transmission I
Description: Low ability to be transmitted through water.

Name: Water Transmission II
Description: Medium ability to be transmitted through water.

Name: Water Transmission III
Description: High ability to be transmitted through water.

Name: Air Transmission I
Description: Low ability to be transmitted through air.

Name: Air Transmission II
Description: Medium ability to be transmitted through air.

Name: Air Transmission III
Description: High ability to be transmitted through air.

Name: Avian Transmission I
Description: Low ability to be transmitted through birds.

Name: Avian Transmission II
Description: Medium ability to be transmitted through birds.

Name: Avian Transmission III
Description: High ability to be transmitted through brids.

Name: Insect Transmission I
Description: Low ability to be transmitted through insects.

Name: Insect Transmission II
Description: Medium ability to be transmitted through insects.

Name: Insect Transmission III
Description: High ability to be transmitted through insects.
